    "name": "Question 39 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "A galvanometer can be converted into an ammeter by connecting a resistor in ___ and the resistor is known as a ___",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "series, shunt",
        "parallel, shunt",
        "series, multiplier",
        "parallel, multiplier"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "parallel, shunt"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<p>A shunt resistor in parallel diverts most current, allowing the galvanometer to measure larger currents. The equivalent resistance is: \\[ \\frac{1}{R_{eq}} = \\frac{1}{R_g} + \\frac{1}{R_{shunt}} \\]</p>"
    },
    "topic": [
