  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 57 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Two resistors \\( R_1 \\) and \\( R_2 \\) are connected in parallel, \\( R_2 \\) being greater than \\( R_1 \\). The combined resistance is",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "less than \\( R_1 \\)",
        "greater than \\( R_1 \\)",
        "sum of \\( R_1 \\) and \\( R_2 \\)",
        "the difference of \\( R_2 \\) and \\( R_1 \\)"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "less than \\( R_1 \\)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "For parallel resistors, the equivalent resistance \\( R_{\\text{eq}} = \\frac{R_1 R_2}{R_1 + R_2} \\). Since \\( R_2 > R_1 \\), \\( R_{\\text{eq}} < R_1 \\) (e.g., if \\( R_1 = 1\\Omega \\) and \\( R_2 = 2\\Omega \\), \\( R_{\\text{eq}} = \\frac{2}{3}\\Omega < 1\\Omega \\))."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Physics",
      "Electromagnetism",
      "Circuit Analysis",
      "Electrical Resistance",
      "Parallel Circuits"
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 68 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "The equivalent capacitance of the system",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "3.3µF",
        "30µF",
        "0.2µF",
        "40µF"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "3.3µF"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "The 3µF and 6µF capacitors are in series: \\( \\frac{1}{C_1} = \\frac{1}{3} + \\frac{1}{6} = \\frac{1}{2} \\), so \\( C_1 = 2\\mu F \\). Similarly, the 2µF and 4µF capacitors are in series: \\( \\frac{1}{C_2} = \\frac{1}{2} + \\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{3}{4} \\), so \\( C_2 = \\frac{4}{3}\\mu F \\approx 1.33\\mu F \\). Then, \\( C_{eq} = C_1 + C_2 = 2\\mu F + 1.33\\mu F \\approx 3.33\\mu F \\approx 3.3\\mu F \\). Thus, the correct answer is 3.3µF."
    },
    "topic": [
